  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "Attending a TED event can vary in cost depending on the type of event you're interested in and its location. Here's a breakdown to help you understand the potential expenses involved:\n\n### 1. **TED Conferences**\n\n**TED Conferences** are the flagship events organized by TED (Technology, Entertainment, Design). These events are known for featuring high-profile speakers and innovative ideas.\n\n- **Cost**: Tickets for TED Conferences can be quite expensive, often ranging from **$7,500 to $10,000 USD** or more per person for general admission. Pricing may vary based on the event location, the level of access, and membership status.\n  \n- **Application Process**: Attendance is usually by invitation or through an application process. TED prioritizes a diverse and global audience, so securing a ticket can be competitive.\n  \n- **Benefits**: Attendees receive access to exclusive talks, networking opportunities with thought leaders, and premium event experiences.\n\n### 2. **TEDx Events**\n\n**TEDx** events are independently organized under license from TED and are designed to bring the TED experience to local communities.\n\n- **Cost**: Tickets for TEDx events are generally **more affordable**, typically ranging from **$50 to $200 USD** depending on the event's scale, location, and exclusivity.\n  \n- **Accessibility**: These events are more accessible to the general public compared to the main TED Conferences. Prices can vary based on factors like venue size, local organizing costs, and specific event offerings.\n  \n- **Benefits**: While smaller in scale, TEDx events still feature inspiring speakers and provide valuable networking opportunities within the local community.\n\n### 3. **Virtual Attendance**\n\nIn response to global changes and to increase accessibility, TED has offered **virtual attendance options** for some events, especially following the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n- **Cost**: Virtual tickets are usually **more affordable**, often ranging from **$100 to $500 USD** depending on the event and the level of interaction or perks included.\n  \n- **Flexibility**: Virtual attendance allows you to participate from anywhere in the world, offering live streaming of talks, interactive sessions, and digital networking opportunities.\n  \n- **Benefits**: Access to recorded sessions post-event, the ability to attend multiple talks without travel, and lower overall costs.\n\n### 4. **Watching TED Talks Online**\n\nIf attending a live event isn't feasible, you can still access a vast library of TED Talks **for free** online.\n\n- **Cost**: **Free**\n  \n- **Accessibility**: Available on the [official TED website](https://www.ted.com/talks) and their YouTube channel, covering a wide range of topics from diverse speakers.\n  \n- **Benefits**: Unlimited access to thousands of talks, the ability to watch at your own pace, and no geographic or financial barriers.\n\n### Additional Considerations\n\n- **Travel and Accommodation**: If you're attending an in-person event, consider additional costs such as travel, accommodation, meals, and local transportation.\n  \n- **Early Bird Discounts**: Some events offer early registration discounts or group rates, which can help reduce the overall cost.\n  \n- **Scholarships and Sponsorships**: Occasionally, TED or local organizing bodies may offer scholarships or sponsorships to help cover ticket costs for individuals who may not afford them otherwise.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nThe cost to attend a TED event varies widely based on the type of event, location, and the level of access you seek. While mainstream TED Conferences are on the higher end of the price spectrum, TEDx events and virtual attendance options provide more affordable alternatives. Additionally, the wealth of free TED Talks available online ensures that you can still engage with inspiring ideas without any financial commitment.\n\nIf you're interested in attending a specific TED or TEDx event, it's a good idea to check the official [TED website](https://www.ted.com/attend) or the respective TEDx event page for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding ticket availability and pricing.",
